article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 62, N. Illinois 59
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio (AP) -- Nathan Peavy scored four of his 19 points in the closing minutes to pull Miami of Ohio ahead, and the RedHawks hung on for a 62-59 win over Northern Illinois on Tuesday night. Miami was trailing 57-56 with 1:51 left when Peavy made a layup and two free throws in a 40-second stretch. Two foul shots by Quintan Lipkins -- his only points of the game -- closed Northern Illinois within one, but the Huskies' Mike McKinney missed a layup with 5 seconds left. Tim Pollitz was fouled getting the rebound for Miami (9-11, 5-3 Mid-American) and made both free throws. Peavy stole the ball with one second left to seal the win. Pollitz finished with 18 points and six rebounds. Peavy had eight rebounds. McKinney had 20 points to lead the Huskies (4-16, 1-7), and Ryan Paradise scored 15. James Hughes added 11 rebounds.
